ducation. Communication is crucial for crew.\n\nCandidate D: problem solving, concentration, responsibility, responds to unexpected events - good. Weaknesses: hot temper, know-it-all attitude - could affect crew.\n\nWhich is best? Possibly Candidate A's technical navigation strengths are critical for long-distance flights. Leadership can help crew. Attitude issues but maybe less severe than others' communication or temper issues. Candidate B's nasty remarks could be severe for teamwork. Candidate C's communication difficulty is also severe. Candidate D's hot temper could be dangerous under stress.\n\nThus provisional preference: Candidate A.\n\nWe should note uncertainties: lack of info on stress handling for A, memory for numbers, etc. Also missing info from other agents about other strengths.\n\nWhat would change vote: if other agents provide evidence that another candidate has strong teamwork and calmness without attitude issues, or that A has poor stress handling.\n\nNow produce output."}
